---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="Getting started">
  <article class="doc">
    <div class="eyebrow">Docs / 01</div>
    <h1>Getting started</h1>
    <p class="intro">Install lawlint, point it at a document, and get a focused list of things worth revising.</p>
    <h2>Install</h2>
    <pre>bun add -d lawlint</pre>
    <h2>Run the CLI</h2>
    <pre>npx lawlint contract.md
cat memo.txt | npx lawlint - --format json</pre>
    <p>Markdown files automatically skip fenced code blocks. For piped Markdown, add <code>--markdown</code>.</p>
    <h2>Scoring</h2>
    <p>Every result includes a human-likeness score from 0 to 100. Each diagnostic charges a penalty — 5 points per error, 3 per warning, 1 per info — normalized per 1,000 words, so the score reflects how <em>dense</em> the issues are rather than how long the document is. The score decays smoothly as penalty density rises (for clean text it behaves like a simple point deduction; heavily flagged text approaches 0 without every bad document flattening to the same score). Density rules such as <code>no-hedging</code> and <code>no-em-dash-overuse</code> charge in proportion to how far past their threshold the text runs.</p>
    <h2>Exit codes</h2>
    <ul><li><code>0</code> when no errors are found and the warning limit is not exceeded.</li><li><code>1</code> when an error is found or <code>--max-warnings</code> is exceeded.</li></ul>
    <p><a href="/docs/cli">Next: CLI reference →</a></p>
  </article>
</Layout>
